  "text": "Bottom-up segmentation methods (e.g. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] ) group low-level cues such as texture, color, or contour continuity, without using any external knowledge about the objects occurring in the image. Some work shows how to learn optimal combinations of cues based on human perceptual judgments to provide robust boundary detection [CITATION_3] .",
